Paramedics arrive
a few minutes after that.

19:09.523 --> 19:13.068
They check her out.
Report she's
six millimeters dilated.

19:13.151 --> 19:16.238
EMT says she ain't had no life
in her heart at all for a while.

19:16.321 --> 19:18.782
Medical Well,
I don't feel any fractures,

19:18.866 --> 19:21.201
but there are
considerable wounds.

19:21.285 --> 19:22.327
If this was a beating,

19:22.411 --> 19:24.079
I'd say you're looking
for something long and hollow.

19:26.164 --> 19:29.418
Sergeant Borden calls me,
wakes me up,

19:29.501 --> 19:30.794
tells me I should
get down to the scene

19:30.878 --> 19:32.170
because there's
a lot of blood.

19:33.297 --> 19:34.131
No sign of forced entry

19:34.214 --> 19:37.593
and, and it don't look
like an accident.

19:41.054 --> 19:43.682
Jim
How much blood?

19:45.559 --> 19:47.185
Like the woman's
head exploded.

19:48.687 --> 19:50.022
Where is this?

19:50.105 --> 19:53.108
Uh, Forest Hills.

19:53.192 --> 19:53.984
I imagine you're gonna be
getting calls about this

19:54.067 --> 19:55.944
when you walk
through the door.

19:56.028 --> 19:57.654
The husband is
Michael Peterson

19:57.738 --> 19:59.823
and the deceased
is his wife Kathleen.

20:02.242 --> 20:03.577
Michael Peterson,
Michael Peterson?

20:03.660 --> 20:07.039
Oh yeah.
That's why I wanted
to give you the heads up.

20:09.291 --> 20:12.002
And you say there is
no sign of a break-in?

20:12.085 --> 20:15.130
Big house,
but don't look like it.

20:15.213 --> 20:17.424
Sounds like no one was here
except for him and his wife.

20:24.514 --> 20:26.433
Thanks for
the heads up, Art.

20:26.516 --> 20:27.142
-Alright, Jim.
-Mm-hmm.

20:29.019 --> 20:29.186
Bye now.

20:33.106 --> 20:36.109
Officer, can I take
my car now, the Subaru?

20:36.193 --> 20:37.527
Yup, you're all clear.

20:37.611 --> 20:38.820
You sure you don't want
to make a statement?

20:38.904 --> 20:40.280
