She's dead.

22:11.788 --> 22:13.582
Jesus, Mike. What--

22:13.665 --> 22:15.709
I need you
to tell Candace and Lori.

22:15.792 --> 22:18.086
Of course. Yeah, uh...

22:18.170 --> 22:19.421
-I'm so sorry--
-Okay, thanks, Mark.

22:27.179 --> 22:29.014
You let me know
if you need anything.

22:29.097 --> 22:30.265
Thanks, Larry.

22:34.394 --> 22:35.896
Dad, have some.

22:35.979 --> 22:37.272
-What?
-Have some.

22:37.355 --> 22:38.523
Uh, no.

22:41.985 --> 22:42.319
Give me those numbers.

22:44.571 --> 22:46.114
I'm going to call
the girls for you.

22:47.324 --> 22:49.034
Yeah.

22:49.117 --> 22:52.037
But don't just call them.
Like, I want someone there

22:52.120 --> 22:54.247
to tell them, you know.

22:54.331 --> 22:56.500
Yeah, I'll call the
sorority house for Caitlin.

22:56.583 --> 22:58.168
I'll try the dorms
for Margaret.

23:00.420 --> 23:02.297
Shit, Margaret.

23:05.092 --> 23:06.802
Is today the ninth?

23:09.971 --> 23:11.807
It's Margaret's
birthday tomorrow.

23:24.569 --> 23:26.238
Oh god,
I hate this, I hate this.

23:26.321 --> 23:26.988
You have no idea, Carol,

23:27.072 --> 23:30.200
how much I hate this.

23:30.283 --> 23:32.160
I mean, I come into the office,
and I don't know

23:32.244 --> 23:33.370
if I'm going to find
an envelope on my desk.

23:33.453 --> 23:35.247
And when I see it,
my heart just...

23:36.123 --> 23:37.999
sinks.

23:38.083 --> 23:40.794
Because inside
is this damn list.

23:40.877 --> 23:42.671
And it's just names,
there's no reason.

23:42.754 --> 23:44.631
I know.

23:44.714 --> 23:46.508
-I know.

23:48.885 --> 23:50.512
I just don't understand.

23:52.305 --> 23:53.223
Did I make a mistake?
Was my work not good?

23:53.306 --> 23:56.518
No. God, no,
it's not that.

23:56.601 --> 24:01.148
It's just the merger
hasn't played out as planned.

24:01.231 --> 24:01.940
And Nortel can't afford
the redundancy.

24:02.023 --> 24:04.192
It's that simple.

24:08.864 --> 24:10.073
The severance package
is okay.

24:10.157 --> 24:11.408
I mean, it'll give you
time to look.

24:13.952 --> 24:14.369
Is Eric still at Glassco?

24:16.329 --> 24:16.580
For now.

24:21.126 --> 24:23.044
Look, it's going
to be okay. I promise.

24:23.128 --> 24:24.379
And if anything
changes here--

24:24.462 --> 24:25.672
Fuck it.

24:30.177 --> 24:32.387
-I'm sorry.
-No, it's okay.

24:43.315 --> 24:45.525
Well, I'm running very simply

24:45.609 --> 24:47.402
because I'm sick of seeing

24:47.485 --> 24:50.322
what these bozos in City Hall
are doing to this town.

24:50.405 --> 24:52.574
So does this
mean we can't expect
any more books from you?

24:52.657 --> 24:54.826
Oh no, I'll always be a writer.

24:54.910 --> 24:57.579
I just finished
my latest column, uh, today,

24:57.662 --> 25:00.332
as a matter of fact about
the Bozo DA Jim Hardin

25:00.415 --> 25:01.750
going after bingo halls
instead of real criminals.

25:01.833 --> 25:04.461
Prior to writing his weekly
column for "The Sun,"

25:04.544 --> 25:07.797
Michael Peterson was
best known as a novelist,

25:07.881 --> 25:09.674
-finding success
writing war novels.
-Oh, and still is.

25:09.758 --> 25:12.761
So I have to ask,
because it's going to come up.

25:12.844 --> 25:14.763
You ran for mayor in '99.

25:14.846 --> 25:16.473
-Oh god, here we go.
-Yes.

25:16.556 --> 25:17.891
-Yeah. Motherfucker.
-You were in the lead

25:17.974 --> 25:18.934
and then a story came out
that you had lied

25:19.017 --> 25:22.103
about receiving
a Purple Heart in Vietnam.

25:22.187 --> 25:24.272
It arguably cost you
the mayorship,

25:24.356 --> 25:26.107
and you hadn't
in fact injured

25:26.191 --> 25:27.609
your leg in combat,
as you claim.

25:27.692 --> 25:30.111
No, I-I-I had been injured

25:30.195 --> 25:31.821
in a car accident
while on duty.

25:31.905 --> 25:36.451
But your injury
was not sustained in combat.

25:36.534 --> 25:38.286
Uh, no, no, it wasn't.

25:39.621 --> 25:41.998
Look, I, I have faith

25:42.082 --> 25:45.085
that the voters will see past
that hiccup in my character.

25:45.168 --> 25:46.628
My opponent,
Howard Clement,

25:46.711 --> 25:47.879
is not going

25:47.963 --> 25:49.923
to bring about
change in Durham.

25:50.006 --> 25:51.299
-I will.
-You... putz!

25:51.383 --> 25:54.135
There will be
several debates in
the coming months...

25:54.219 --> 25:55.637
-Papa needs practice.

25:57.305 --> 25:58.974
...before hitting the polls
November sixth.

26:04.562 --> 26:06.439
Hmm.

26:06.439 --> 26:06.523
Hello.

26:08.066 --> 26:08.984
Hey.

26:10.235 --> 26:11.528
Uh, I'm, I'm good. You?

26:13.863 --> 26:17.284
So are we, uh,
we set for the fifth?

26:18.952 --> 26:20.537
Oh, well, you're coming
from, uh, from where again?

26:22.914 --> 26:23.790
Yeah, well, uh,

26:23.873 --> 26:26.543
either the, the hotel
by the airport there

26:26.626 --> 26:28.420
or, or at my place.

26:30.505 --> 26:31.589
Mm-hmm.

26:32.132 --> 26:34.009
Yeah.

26:34.092 --> 26:36.011
Well, you ready
to get that ass pounded?

26:39.306 --> 26:41.766
Hmm.
Well, alright, then.

26:45.145 --> 26:47.522
Hey, Mike?
Can you give me
a hand with dinner?

26:56.906 --> 26:58.199
I kept an eye
on the stock market today.

26:58.283 --> 27:00.994
Nortel was holding steady.

27:01.077 --> 27:02.245
That's a good sign.

27:02.329 --> 27:04.664
Mm, it's positive.
Yeah.

27:04.748 --> 27:07.334
As long as the company keeps
its head above water.

27:08.835 --> 27:11.212
I mean, you'd think
with all I've built there,

27:11.296 --> 27:13.048
I'd be secure,
but who knows.

27:13.131 --> 27:15.717
We're fine, Kathleen.
We're fine.

27:19.304 --> 27:21.056
Maybe we should let
Essy go for a while

27:21.139 --> 27:23.308
and save some money.
Hmm?

27:23.391 --> 27:24.726
Shouldn't be too hard
to keep the house clean

27:24.809 --> 27:26.353
-without the kids around.
-Hm.

27:59.010 --> 28:01.346
Medical
We've got blood embedded
under the nails.

28:01.429 --> 28:03.640
There were no defensive
wounds on the husband.

28:04.724 --> 28:06.559
-It could be her own.
-Hm.

28:06.643 --> 28:08.103
We've got something
between the fingers.

28:08.186 --> 28:10.188
Can I get the tweezers?

28:10.271 --> 28:10.814
Here you go.

28:16.027 --> 28:18.196
Medical
Looks like a pine needle.

28:18.279 --> 28:19.114
Pine needle?

28:19.197 --> 28:22.367
Bag it for evidence.

28:22.450 --> 28:22.826
Okay.

28:32.919 --> 28:34.754
Medical
Looks like this is her own hair.

28:36.714 --> 28:37.674
Let's bag it and test it.

28:42.178 --> 28:43.138
Feel this.

28:43.221 --> 28:44.973
Feel this gently.

28:45.056 --> 28:47.016
Gently.

28:48.685 --> 28:51.646
This is
the superior cornu
of the left thyroid.

28:51.729 --> 28:54.732
Until I get in there
I can't say for sure but

28:54.816 --> 28:56.985
I'm guessing she
didn't die right away.

28:57.068 --> 28:58.945
She struggled.

29:16.463 --> 29:18.131
Medical
Gentle.

29:28.600 --> 29:30.685
Uncle Bill's here, Dad.

29:30.768 --> 29:32.562
Clayton is pulling up now.

29:34.939 --> 29:36.191
I'm so sorry.

29:37.108 --> 29:38.276
I'm so sorry.

29:40.987 --> 29:41.946
Okay.

29:48.495 --> 29:48.745
Mike.

29:53.333 --> 29:53.833
Uh, I'm gonna...

29:55.627 --> 29:57.712
ask you
this question and...

30:01.883 --> 30:04.719
no matter what the answer is,
it stays in this room.

30:04.802 --> 30:05.803
Jesus Christ.

30:09.474 --> 30:11.309
-No.
-I'm sorry, I'm...

30:13.102 --> 30:14.646
I mean, I don't know
why I even...

30:17.690 --> 30:19.150
From what you've told me,

30:20.318 --> 30:22.153
it sounds like
they think you did,

30:22.237 --> 30:25.323
so we, we need
to get you a lawyer.

30:26.658 --> 30:27.992
Can't you represent him?

30:28.076 --> 30:29.827
No, I-I-I do estates.

30:29.911 --> 30:31.037
I don't do criminal law.

30:31.120 --> 30:32.747
I certainly can't do
criminal law in Durham.

30:34.999 --> 30:36.834
How about Larry?

30:36.918 --> 30:39.963
I don't think
Larry's tough enough.

30:41.005 --> 30:42.507
What about, um, the guy

30:42.590 --> 30:46.219
the one you considered

30:46.302 --> 30:47.387
before Clay went away
for spring break.

30:47.470 --> 30:49.889
-Oh, David Rudolf?
-Yeah.

30:49.973 --> 30:51.307
Fuck, Bill.

30:51.391 --> 30:53.434
He's the kind of guy
you get when you're guilty.

30:53.518 --> 30:54.269
Well, he's,
he's, he's smart.

30:54.352 --> 30:56.813
He's really smart.

30:56.896 --> 30:59.065
He, he, he's not
one of those,

30:59.148 --> 31:00.441
you know,
good ol' boys,

31:00.525 --> 31:02.277
like so many
of the guys down here.

31:05.613 --> 31:07.031
Have you told the girls?

31:07.115 --> 31:10.285
Todd called the school.
There's someone there.

31:10.368 --> 31:12.328
-Shit.

31:12.412 --> 31:12.787
The cake.

31:15.873 --> 31:18.585
I need you to go get
a cake for Margaret.

31:19.168 --> 31:20.295
What do you mean?

31:23.590 --> 31:25.633
It's the funeral home.

31:28.678 --> 31:30.013
Thank you.

31:30.096 --> 31:31.222
Hello?

31:33.725 --> 31:35.476
I need you to get
a cake for Margaret.

31:35.560 --> 31:36.185
I'm going to stay here
with Dad.

31:36.269 --> 31:37.270
No, seriously.
Not right now.

31:37.353 --> 31:39.647
You're my kid brother,
don't tell me what to do.

31:39.731 --> 31:41.274
I'm not telling you
what to do, Clay.

31:42.400 --> 31:44.360
I'm asking for
some help here. Please.

31:44.444 --> 31:44.861
Yeah. Alright.

31:47.614 --> 31:49.032
Don't fucking
snap at me like that.

31:51.618 --> 31:54.078
I was the one that was
there and saw Kathleen
all fucking dead

31:54.162 --> 31:55.496
and fucking covered
in blood and shit.

31:55.580 --> 31:55.830
Alright, alright!

31:57.999 --> 31:59.334
I've kept my shit together.

31:59.417 --> 32:01.044
Alright, I get it.
I'm sorry, man.

32:18.561 --> 32:21.648
The, uh...
funeral home said that

32:21.731 --> 32:24.025
the autopsy was
more thorough than expected.

32:24.108 --> 32:24.942
Jesus Christ.

32:25.026 --> 32:27.945
Just as soon as they
started working on her,

32:28.029 --> 32:29.572
the police came back.

32:29.656 --> 32:32.241
Apparently,
the cops found an, uh,

32:33.368 --> 32:35.244
open condom
in your bedroom.

32:36.204 --> 32:40.124
And they decided
to perform a rape test.

32:41.876 --> 32:43.044
A rape test?

32:43.961 --> 32:46.673
What condom?
We didn't use condoms.

32:51.678 --> 32:52.095
It's a witch hunt.

32:55.264 --> 32:57.058
Kathleen said it.
She said, "Mike,

32:57.141 --> 33:00.520
"stop going after City Hall,
the DA, and the cops.

33:00.603 --> 33:00.895
It's gonna
bite you in the ass."

33:03.856 --> 33:06.776
Revenge, Bill,
that's what this is.

33:08.986 --> 33:10.863
There were
35 total cuts,

33:10.947 --> 33:12.949
wounds, and contusions
on her body.

33:13.032 --> 33:16.994
Seven lacerations alone
on the posterior scalp.

33:19.497 --> 33:22.750
The rape test
came back negative.

33:22.834 --> 33:25.586
No bruising or contusions
around the vagina or anus.

33:25.670 --> 33:28.965
Chief Medical
What do you think about
the broken superior cornu

33:29.048 --> 33:30.258
of the left thyroid?

33:30.341 --> 33:33.761
Could indicate strangulation,
but it's not conclusive.

33:35.513 --> 33:37.432
Now, what I
can't explain is

33:37.515 --> 33:40.727
why there are
no skull fractures.

33:40.810 --> 33:42.437
That's what you would
normally see in a beating.

33:44.188 --> 33:46.274
You didn't put in
the cause of death?

33:46.357 --> 33:48.109
I did.

33:48.192 --> 33:49.444
She bled out.

33:50.862 --> 33:51.946
Without skull fracture,
blunt force trauma--

33:52.029 --> 33:55.408
Someone holding something
caused the impact

33:55.491 --> 33:56.284
to make these wounds.

33:56.367 --> 33:58.786
That's not for me
to conclude in here.

33:58.870 --> 34:00.788
You think the murder weapon
just flew through the air

34:00.872 --> 34:02.373
held by no one?

34:03.833 --> 34:05.710
I mean,
you can leave as is

34:05.793 --> 34:07.295
or make any changes
you see fit

34:07.378 --> 34:09.213
based on what I just said.

34:09.297 --> 34:11.841
Hardin wants to get this
to SBI sooner than later.

34:25.062 --> 34:26.564
Have you given
a statement?

34:27.607 --> 34:29.942
Uh, no.
Nothing official.

34:30.026 --> 34:31.152
Just, uh,

34:31.235 --> 34:33.905
you know, I told them
I came in and, um,

34:33.988 --> 34:35.490
I found her there.

34:36.991 --> 34:39.202
You didn't hear
or see anything?

34:39.285 --> 34:41.829
I have to take this.
It's, uh, Todd.

34:42.622 --> 34:44.791
Hey, Todd.

34:44.874 --> 34:46.584
-So...
-I just found her there.

34:46.667 --> 34:49.045
She, she was breathing.

34:51.172 --> 34:52.632
And then she wasn't.

34:53.883 --> 34:57.845
How long between
when she left you

34:57.929 --> 34:59.806
-to when you found her?
-I don't know.

34:59.889 --> 35:01.641
It couldn't be
more than half an hour.

35:03.476 --> 35:05.812
You didn't hear her scream,
call your name or?

35:05.895 --> 35:07.688
I, I didn't hear
a goddamn thing.

35:11.275 --> 35:12.485
Alright.

35:20.618 --> 35:21.118
You know Rae Carruth?

35:23.162 --> 35:24.121
-The football player.
-Yeah, of course, I do.

35:25.957 --> 35:27.792
I represented him
last October.

35:27.875 --> 35:29.126
-Yeah, I know.
-Hmm.

35:29.210 --> 35:31.504
Case had a lot
of moving parts,

35:31.587 --> 35:33.172
multiple charges.

35:36.008 --> 35:38.427
He-he shot
his pregnant girlfriend.

35:38.511 --> 35:40.888
All I'm saying is,
we helped him quite a bit.

35:40.972 --> 35:43.099
Got him a vastly
reduced sentence.

35:45.268 --> 35:48.855
Though God willing,
you won't need any help.

35:48.938 --> 35:53.818
But sometimes good people
get dragged into situations

35:53.901 --> 35:55.194
that turn out bad.

35:55.278 --> 35:56.112
Okay. So...

35:58.698 --> 36:01.576
how much is it going to cost?

36:01.659 --> 36:03.452
A case like this,
you're going to need

36:03.536 --> 36:05.496
jury consultants,
blood analysts.

36:05.580 --> 36:07.999
Between four
and five hundred K.

36:08.082 --> 36:09.542
Half a million bucks.

36:09.625 --> 36:11.252
I've got five kids
to worry about, you know.

36:11.335 --> 36:12.587
Three still in college.

36:12.670 --> 36:14.338
Good defense isn't cheap.

36:14.422 --> 36:17.300
I shouldn't need a defense.
I shouldn't even be here.

36:19.552 --> 36:22.013
Does Kathleen have
life insurance?

36:22.638 --> 36:23.472
-Savings?
-Yes.

36:23.556 --> 36:25.683
So...

36:27.393 --> 36:29.604
When it comes
to staying out of prison,

36:29.687 --> 36:30.104
anything's up for grabs.

36:33.232 --> 36:34.358
Sorry about that.

36:35.276 --> 36:37.236
Martha and Caitlin
are here.

36:37.320 --> 36:38.696
Candace and Lori too.

36:38.779 --> 36:40.907
So we're going
to meet at Larry's.

36:40.990 --> 36:42.950
Okay. Then maybe
I shouldn't keep you.

36:44.243 --> 36:46.162
-Did you two...
-Yeah, yeah, we're, uh...

36:51.167 --> 36:52.585
Well, um...

36:55.046 --> 36:57.506
regardless of whether
or not you, um,

36:57.590 --> 37:00.760
end up hiring me,
one piece of advice:

37:00.843 --> 37:01.844
keep your family close.

37:01.928 --> 37:04.055
You'll need them
on your side.

37:04.889 --> 37:06.641
-Thank you.
-Of course,

37:06.724 --> 37:08.059
-Nice to meet you.
-You too.

37:24.951 --> 37:26.577
-That was fast.
-Yeah.

37:28.579 --> 37:29.747
What do you think?

37:32.792 --> 37:34.543
I don't know.

37:34.627 --> 37:36.337
My guy over
at the Durham station

37:36.420 --> 37:39.423
says the crime scene photos
are a goddamn nightmare.

37:39.507 --> 37:41.884
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

37:41.968 --> 37:44.428
But autopsy
isn't back yet, so...

37:44.512 --> 37:47.056
-We'll see.
-911 call?

37:47.139 --> 37:48.557
Sounds like he's in shock.

37:49.850 --> 37:51.435
It doesn't feel like
an act to me.

37:54.438 --> 37:55.982
Pastrami any good here?

38:00.152 --> 38:00.319
Hmm.

38:12.248 --> 38:13.624
They're all in here.

38:15.626 --> 38:16.919
-- Margaret.
-- I'm sorry.

38:17.003 --> 38:18.129
I'm sorry.

38:18.212 --> 38:20.047
My flight got canceled

38:20.131 --> 38:22.550
'cause of some terror scare.

38:22.633 --> 38:23.384
Are you okay?

38:23.467 --> 38:25.344
Yeah,
yeah, I just wanted

38:25.428 --> 38:26.762
to get to you guys.

38:40.651 --> 38:41.736
Ask him.

38:47.700 --> 38:48.659
Mike, what's goin' on?

38:48.743 --> 38:50.870
Um...

38:50.953 --> 38:52.663
Lori and I are feeling

38:52.747 --> 38:54.665
a little in the dark over here.

38:55.166 --> 38:56.834
About what?

38:59.211 --> 39:01.172
Uh, what happened?

39:02.673 --> 39:04.300
Well, she fell.

39:07.053 --> 39:09.597
Yeah, but it was
our sister's last night.

39:09.680 --> 39:11.098
Can we talk
about this later?

39:11.182 --> 39:13.225
We would really like
to do this now.

39:13.309 --> 39:15.770
-Could you just say more--
-I just sold a book

39:15.853 --> 39:17.146
to a producer
in Hollywood.

39:18.981 --> 39:21.108
With everything going on
at Nortel, it, it...

39:23.194 --> 39:26.530
was, uh, it was good
to have some good news.

39:28.365 --> 39:29.366
Um...

39:31.535 --> 39:35.289
I went, I went to Blockbuster,
got a movie.

39:35.373 --> 39:38.793
"America's Sweethearts."
It was so dumb.

39:38.876 --> 39:40.544
Kathleen was,
was cracking up.

39:44.340 --> 39:45.466
And, uh...

39:47.468 --> 39:48.552
it was a nice day.

39:51.639 --> 39:52.723
And then Todd came by.

39:53.891 --> 39:54.767
Yeah, around- 00.

39:56.060 --> 39:57.603
I was meeting
a friend there at the house,

39:57.686 --> 39:58.521
and we were going
to this Christmas party.

40:01.107 --> 40:03.776
Mom was
pretty tipsy already.

40:07.404 --> 40:10.783
When they left,
Kathleen got a, a call

40:10.866 --> 40:11.700
about a work email.

40:11.784 --> 40:14.995
She was, she was annoyed
that she'd have to,

40:15.079 --> 40:16.622
you know, wake up early.

40:16.705 --> 40:20.960
But it was a Saturday,
and we were having a nice night.

40:21.043 --> 40:22.837
So we went out to the pool,

40:22.920 --> 40:27.508
and, uh... we just smoked
and talked,

40:27.591 --> 40:29.593
you know, about the kids,
about Christmas.

40:32.138 --> 40:34.181
And then she said,
"I have to go up.

40:35.766 --> 40:37.226
I have that call
in the morning."

40:40.396 --> 40:40.563
And that was it.

40:45.568 --> 40:48.529
I went in later,
and I found her laying there.

40:48.612 --> 40:50.739
But what are the police
looking for?

40:50.823 --> 40:52.992
Oh, I have no idea.

40:53.075 --> 40:55.119
You know, the cops
around here, they hated me

40:55.202 --> 40:57.371
ever since I started
writing in the local paper.

40:59.874 --> 41:01.959
You know, I tried to expose
what's going on in this town,

41:02.042 --> 41:04.628
and that they-- and now
they're torturing us.

41:04.712 --> 41:06.589
They've been awful.

41:06.672 --> 41:09.258
I've never seen anything
like it in my 30 years of law.

41:18.893 --> 41:20.394
Um, will you pass
the mashed potatoes, please.

41:30.613 --> 41:33.115
Candace, are you sure
you don't need a place to stay?

41:33.199 --> 41:35.367
No, thank you.

41:35.451 --> 41:38.120
We're good. Uh, I booked us
a room at the, uh...

41:40.164 --> 41:42.917
the inn there
in Chapel Hill, so...

41:43.000 --> 41:44.793
Let us know
if you change your mind.

41:44.877 --> 41:46.086
Thank you, Larry.

41:48.172 --> 41:49.423
Should we, um...

41:51.175 --> 41:54.303
Mike, have you thought
about the wake?

41:54.386 --> 41:57.306
We're, we're all set
at the Howerton Bryan?

41:57.389 --> 41:58.641
-It's a nice place.
-Okay.

42:00.643 --> 42:02.311
Uh, how about music?

42:02.394 --> 42:03.979
We could play
The Mills Brothers.

42:04.063 --> 42:06.440
That's nice.

42:06.523 --> 42:07.441
-What song?
-"You Always"--

42:11.195 --> 42:13.739
Any really. She loved,
she loved them all.

42:13.822 --> 42:15.282
Great idea.

42:16.367 --> 42:17.785
What is going on?

42:42.893 --> 42:46.313
Kathleen would have wanted
you to have some cake.

42:46.397 --> 42:48.065
Even with everything
going on.

43:06.333 --> 43:07.626
Let's just get
the photos and go.

43:22.391 --> 43:25.311
Should we get
out of here?

43:25.394 --> 43:26.603
It's kind of nice in here
with all of her stuff.

43:55.549 --> 43:58.052
What is that?

43:58.135 --> 44:02.139
It's a song I was going
to suggest to play.

44:03.640 --> 44:04.641
I almost blurted it out.

44:07.561 --> 44:11.690
"You Always Hurt
the One You Love."

44:11.774 --> 44:12.775
-Lori...
-What?

44:14.693 --> 44:15.861
It's a good song.

44:18.322 --> 44:20.824
-Kathleen loved it.
-I know.

44:23.702 --> 44:25.579
Why didn't he
tell us himself?

44:28.540 --> 44:30.834
Why call our husbands?

44:30.918 --> 44:34.213
Imagine him having
to say that to us.

44:42.179 --> 44:43.680
I mean, he's a mess.

44:47.017 --> 44:50.854
We're just all going to be
a mess for a while.

45:46.160 --> 45:47.619
It's a great idea, you know.

45:47.703 --> 45:51.123
We've got all this time.
We can do what we want.

45:51.206 --> 45:54.918
I told you that having
an empty nest was fun.

45:55.002 --> 45:55.502
Oh, come on.

45:55.586 --> 45:57.588
We would party like this

45:57.671 --> 45:58.505
with the kids upstairs too.

45:58.589 --> 46:01.467
That must be
where they get it from.

46:03.802 --> 46:06.346
-Oh, you want a sip?
-I do.

46:06.430 --> 46:08.182
I think. Yes.

46:08.265 --> 46:08.765
Thank you.

46:10.851 --> 46:12.728
You're so polite.
Thank you.

46:13.770 --> 46:14.855
Oh, man.

46:15.564 --> 46:16.940
Okay. Come on.

46:17.983 --> 46:21.487
...amazing,
and good culture, too.

46:21.570 --> 46:24.072
You know, we were
at this Italian restaurant

46:24.156 --> 46:26.074
in, uh, in Miami,

46:26.158 --> 46:27.701
and it was in, um...

46:27.784 --> 46:30.370
What was the name
of that neighborhood?

46:30.454 --> 46:31.705
Uh, it was Miami.

46:31.788 --> 46:35.417
Uh, yes, dear, yes.
It, it was Miami.

46:36.210 --> 46:39.004
-She's, uh...
-What? Shut up.

46:39.087 --> 46:40.005
Uh, fuck it,
doesn't matter.

46:40.088 --> 46:44.468
So, uh, so anyway, we,
I was waiting for my Pino,

46:44.551 --> 46:47.554
and, and she was waiting
for the Mexican Coke.

46:47.638 --> 46:49.765
Which is just a Coke
with real sugar

46:49.848 --> 46:50.891
and not that corn syrup.

46:50.974 --> 46:52.559
-Yeah, it's better.
-Uh, okay, so anyhow.

46:52.643 --> 46:54.686
And then,
then the boss comes over.

46:54.770 --> 46:57.189
And he's holding
a bottle of Coke,

46:57.272 --> 47:00.067
and I swear to God
he presents it

47:00.150 --> 47:01.443
like, like it was
a bottle of wine.

47:01.527 --> 47:03.570
And he says,
no, very seriously,

47:03.654 --> 47:06.657
"We did not have
the Coke from Mexico.

47:06.740 --> 47:09.451
This Coke is
from Atlanta."

47:11.578 --> 47:14.414
Hey, who wants
to go swimming?

47:14.498 --> 47:15.832
What are you
talking about?

47:17.668 --> 47:19.962
Don't be ridiculous.

47:22.673 --> 47:25.551
-Kathleen Peterson, everyone!

47:28.595 --> 47:31.265
Mike, something's wrong.

47:41.650 --> 47:43.193
What's going on?

47:44.361 --> 47:46.363
What happened?

47:48.031 --> 47:51.076
Two planes just crashed
into the World Trade Center.

47:53.662 --> 47:56.540
Reporter
This was after the first
airplane made impact.

47:56.623 --> 47:58.917
We'll be hearing
from the president
in a little while...

47:59.001 --> 48:00.419
This is really bad.

48:00.502 --> 48:01.962
Reporter
...the White House
knows about this,

48:02.045 --> 48:03.130
which appears
to be deliberate.

48:03.213 --> 48:05.382
Reporter
Do you know whether
or not officials

48:05.465 --> 48:07.384
there at the White House
have been made aware...

48:10.387 --> 48:12.639
-Everybody's waiting.
-I can't see her like that.

48:15.309 --> 48:17.227
Here.

48:18.604 --> 48:19.896
You can't be...

48:20.397 --> 48:21.607
seen absent.

48:21.690 --> 48:22.899
You know, Rudolf's smart,

48:22.983 --> 48:26.820
but I don't want
to go down that road.

48:26.903 --> 48:28.780
The last thing I want to do now
is bankrupt the family.

48:28.864 --> 48:30.490
No.

48:30.574 --> 48:32.826
I'm just saying
if there's a grand jury...

48:32.909 --> 48:33.660
You know, this would be
a lot easier if you stood up.

48:33.744 --> 48:36.163
I didn't do
anything wrong.

48:36.246 --> 48:39.958
Okay. Well, I will look
for an alternative tomorrow.

48:40.042 --> 48:43.045
You know, if it comes
to it, we'll have somebody

48:43.128 --> 48:44.504
who's ready,
somebody who's not going

48:44.588 --> 48:46.340
to cost NFL player money.

48:48.800 --> 48:49.760
Hey.

48:49.843 --> 48:51.428
There's cops downstairs.

48:58.352 --> 48:59.436
Haven't you
already searched?

48:59.519 --> 49:02.814
Yes, sir. This is just
a follow-up search.

49:02.898 --> 49:05.275
All very standard practice
in this kind of case.

49:19.289 --> 49:20.499
Mr. Peterson.

49:21.291 --> 49:23.377
-Mr. Peterson,
-Do you mind?!

49:23.460 --> 49:24.294
I'm getting dressed
to go see my dead wife

49:24.378 --> 49:26.380
in a coffin!

49:26.463 --> 49:28.048
Calm down.
Take a breath.

50:26.565 --> 50:28.734
Oh, Ronnie.

50:40.328 --> 50:40.829
Mike.

51:27.751 --> 51:29.669
I'm going to grab a drink.

51:29.753 --> 51:32.380
Can you grab the bags?

51:32.464 --> 51:33.131
I shouldn't
hang out here long.

51:37.135 --> 51:39.012
Bill! Come here!

51:39.096 --> 51:41.139
What?
What's going on?

51:41.223 --> 51:42.307
Just Bill.

51:44.351 --> 51:46.394
-What's going on?
-Shut the door.

51:49.981 --> 51:54.027
Jesus Christ.
Look at this mess.

51:54.110 --> 51:56.613
-What are these guys
looking for?
-They took the computer.

51:59.991 --> 52:01.952
They must have printed
this out before they left.

52:21.805 --> 52:23.473
Was there a lot
of this stuff on there?

52:26.268 --> 52:28.436
I saved images
from an article.

52:38.655 --> 52:39.197
Michael.

52:41.449 --> 52:42.534
This is a message.

52:44.452 --> 52:45.704
"We got you."

52:47.664 --> 52:48.164
I'm cooked.

52:51.877 --> 52:52.961
No.

52:54.296 --> 52:55.672
I'm home cooking.

53:00.927 --> 53:02.304
David
The phone!

53:04.598 --> 53:05.765
It's for you!

53:05.849 --> 53:07.893
-No one calls me this late.
-Charlene!

53:07.976 --> 53:09.227
Get the phone!

53:09.311 --> 53:10.186
Ugh!

53:13.565 --> 53:14.733
Hello?

53:15.483 --> 53:16.610
Yes.

53:16.693 --> 53:18.612
Yes, just a moment,
please.

53:19.529 --> 53:20.530
It's for you.

53:22.532 --> 53:23.116
Really?

53:25.035 --> 53:25.243
Thanks.

53:28.872 --> 53:30.040
Fuck.

53:32.542 --> 53:34.294
Shit.

53:39.799 --> 53:43.470
Dave Rudolf.

53:43.553 --> 53:46.306
David, it's Michael Peterson.

53:46.389 --> 53:47.849
I need your help.

53:47.933 --> 53:50.894
Alright, lock and load.

53:50.977 --> 53:52.354
Are we ready, boys?

53:52.437 --> 53:53.647
Fred.

53:54.648 --> 53:56.775
You want to join us
for the grand jury.

54:00.236 --> 54:02.989
Freda, if the grand jury
goes our way,

54:03.073 --> 54:06.076
I don't just want you
on the team.

54:06.159 --> 54:08.036
You'll be my right hand.

54:08.119 --> 54:10.205
We need
a strong, fierce

54:10.288 --> 54:12.832
feminine presence
on this case.

54:12.916 --> 54:13.375
And that's you.

54:17.671 --> 54:19.381
Is that
Kathleen's autopsy?

54:19.464 --> 54:20.548
-Hmm.
-I've seen it.

54:21.341 --> 54:23.760
You show it
to the family?

54:23.843 --> 54:25.845
No, I haven't made
that call yet.

54:25.929 --> 54:27.555
Uh, but this isn't
the autopsy.

54:27.639 --> 54:29.391
This... no, this is
something else.

54:31.726 --> 54:34.020
See that guy over there?
David Rudolf.

54:34.104 --> 54:35.355
High-priced lawyer

54:35.438 --> 54:37.190
from Chapel Hill
by way of New York.

54:40.193 --> 54:41.695
What a fuckin' prick.

54:49.911 --> 54:51.705
Good morning.

54:51.788 --> 54:53.248
I'm Jim Hardin,

54:53.331 --> 54:56.876
District Attorney
for Durham County.

54:56.960 --> 54:59.212
And I'm here to present
the case of the people

54:59.295 --> 55:00.296
against
Michael Iver Peterson.

55:02.132 --> 55:03.466
And when I'm done,

55:03.550 --> 55:06.177
I'm going to ask
all of you to vote

55:06.261 --> 55:08.346
on one count of murder

55:08.430 --> 55:10.306
in the first degree.

55:22.318 --> 55:23.486
Hello.

55:24.529 --> 55:26.781
Hey, Mike. It's David.

55:26.865 --> 55:29.784
I'm sorry, Mike,
they're going to indict.

55:29.868 --> 55:33.663
You'll have to turn yourself
in to the police this evening.

55:35.790 --> 55:36.958
Alright, David.

55:37.042 --> 55:38.251
Um...

55:40.170 --> 55:43.757
Uh... alright, um, Mike--

55:43.840 --> 55:45.050
No.

55:46.634 --> 55:49.554
Ask him if there's a chance
they can get you out on bail.

55:49.637 --> 55:53.141
Tell, um, tell Bill we're
going to do what we can,

55:53.224 --> 55:55.101
but, uh,
it's the holidays.

55:55.185 --> 55:58.271
It could take
a little while.

55:58.354 --> 56:00.398
I've, um,
I've alerted the media.

56:00.482 --> 56:03.902
We need to be one step
ahead of the DA now.

56:03.985 --> 56:08.198
You and your family need
to make a statement

56:09.032 --> 56:10.617
In order of importance,

56:10.700 --> 56:13.161
it's, uh, Kathleen's
actual biological family

56:13.244 --> 56:15.914
that they need
to hear from.

56:17.373 --> 56:19.793
We, um, really need
Caitlin to speak.

56:19.876 --> 56:22.587
Okay, David.

56:22.670 --> 56:25.924
Okay? Alright.
And, Mike, Mike?

56:26.007 --> 56:28.968
Bring some money,
like 50 bucks

56:29.052 --> 56:32.555
for the commissary
and bring a Bible.

56:32.639 --> 56:34.140
-Bible?
-If you've got one.

56:34.224 --> 56:35.809
I'd rather bring
a fucking Quran.

56:35.892 --> 56:36.976
Well, um,

56:37.060 --> 56:39.813
it's optics at this point.

56:39.896 --> 56:41.272
It's, um, it's, it's important.

56:41.356 --> 56:44.526
Okay. Okay,
whatever you say,

56:44.609 --> 56:48.655
-Alright. Alright.
-Okay, I'll see you there.

56:48.738 --> 56:49.405
Alright. See you here.

56:53.535 --> 56:55.829
Well... that's it.

58:33.843 --> 58:35.887
Over here, everybody.

58:48.483 --> 58:50.610
Kathleen was my life.

58:50.693 --> 58:55.156
I've whispered her name
in my heart a thousand times.

58:55.240 --> 58:56.491
She is there,
but I can't stop crying.

58:58.618 --> 59:02.705
I would never have done
anything to hurt her.

59:02.789 --> 59:04.332
I am innocent
of these charges,

59:04.415 --> 59:07.126
and we will prove it
in court.

59:08.211 --> 59:10.004
We do not want you
to say anything

59:10.088 --> 59:11.381
against your family.

59:11.464 --> 59:13.549
That's not our intent.

59:13.633 --> 59:15.426
We just would like

59:15.510 --> 59:17.720
the opportunity
to present to you

59:17.804 --> 59:19.514
what we have learned

59:19.597 --> 59:21.975
so that you,
as Kathleen's family,

59:22.058 --> 59:23.476
aren't out of the loop,
so to speak.

59:25.853 --> 59:28.398
We have some photos
we'd like to share.

59:29.315 --> 59:31.150
Freda
They're pretty shocking.

59:32.068 --> 59:33.695
You can say,
"No, uh-uh,

59:33.778 --> 59:35.989
"we don't need
to see that, Freda.

59:36.072 --> 59:38.658
Thank you very much."

59:38.741 --> 59:41.953
But we just feel y'all deserve
the right to make that choice.

59:46.165 --> 59:48.501
We, we'd like to see 'em.

59:56.426 --> 59:59.345
My mother and Mike had

59:59.429 --> 1:00:03.516
an absolutely
loving relationship,

1:00:03.599 --> 1:00:04.225
and there is,
there's no way that

1:00:04.309 --> 1:00:06.602
either of them
would ever wish

1:00:06.686 --> 1:00:08.438
any sort of harm
on the other one.

1:00:08.521 --> 1:00:10.523
My mother would be
absolutely appalled.

1:00:13.901 --> 1:00:14.360
Thank you.
That's all.

1:00:22.118 --> 1:00:25.747
There were 35 cuts
and bruises.

1:00:28.291 --> 1:00:29.959
And seven...

1:00:32.003 --> 1:00:33.338
of these

1:00:34.464 --> 1:00:36.591
deep lacerations
to the scalp.

1:00:37.175 --> 1:00:40.762
How... I don't...

1:00:41.721 --> 1:00:45.850
Our autopsy shows
the cause of death

1:00:45.933 --> 1:00:47.560
was blunt force trauma.

1:00:50.063 --> 1:00:52.231
A homicide.

1:00:54.901 --> 1:00:58.363
And we believe Mr. Peterson

1:00:58.446 --> 1:01:02.408
bludgeoned Kathleen to death
and may have strangled her.

1:01:02.492 --> 1:01:04.577
Why would he do that?
It doesn't make sense.

1:01:08.331 --> 1:01:12.627
Our officers found
countless images,

1:01:12.710 --> 1:01:13.669
like these...

1:01:15.129 --> 1:01:18.132
on his computer
and in his desk.

1:01:18.216 --> 1:01:19.759
And we believe

1:01:21.469 --> 1:01:27.016
your sister found these
on his computer that night.

1:01:27.100 --> 1:01:29.560
And she confronted
your brother-in-law about it,

1:01:29.644 --> 1:01:31.896
and a fight ensued.

1:01:42.156 --> 1:01:43.449
What?

1:01:43.533 --> 1:01:44.826
Oh my god...

1:01:48.704 --> 1:01:49.831
It doesn't make sense.

1:01:51.207 --> 1:01:51.749
I knew it.

1:01:53.042 --> 1:01:54.836
I knew it.

1:01:56.212 --> 1:01:57.797
I knew
he was hiding something

1:01:57.880 --> 1:01:59.048
when he didn't have
the nerve to call us himself.

1:01:59.132 --> 1:02:01.050
I knew it.

1:02:05.096 --> 1:02:06.347
Hey...

1:02:08.474 --> 1:02:09.559
We couldn't sleep.

1:02:15.731 --> 1:02:17.400
We've heard
so many wonderful stories

1:02:17.483 --> 1:02:20.278
about our sister
this past week.

1:02:21.571 --> 1:02:24.949
I just can't imagine
she would have accepted

1:02:25.908 --> 1:02:27.827
this in her home.

1:02:32.498 --> 1:02:33.666
In her marriage.

